{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9cab8425-155b-4079-811c-c9c0e3e160fa","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net test project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — it now uses MTP under the hood.\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` replaces `xunit.runner.visualstudio` as the test host\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property enables `dotnet test` integration with MTP\n- Your test code (`[Fact]`, `[Theory]`, etc.) stays unchanged\n- You can also run the test project directly as an executable (`dotnet run` or the built `.exe`)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ff814f2c-a80d-44c9-b1e9-8254cf71f206","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":344,"requestId":"0BDE:155F80:20159C:25AD73:69F004CC"},"id":"8039f76d-7a76-430e-921a-be9b88fb512b","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:52:36.688Z","parentId":"c7bd401d-69ea-426e-a0d7-16e11123478f"}
